# create-foundation-gcp

CLI tool to create a GCP foundation structure with folders, projects, and required APIs enabled.

## Overview

This tool helps you quickly set up a Google Cloud Platform (GCP) foundation with the necessary folders, projects, and APIs enabled for a given company. The structure includes separate environments for development, UAT, production, and common resources.

## Installation

1. **Clone the Repository:**

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/JoaoVasc/create-foundation-gcp.git
   cd create-foundation-gcp

2. **Install the Package Globally:**

  ```bash
      npm install -g .
      npx github:JoaoVasc/create-foundation-gcp <company_name>

3 **Directory Struture**
    foundation-<company_name>
    ├── modules
    │   ├── folder
    │   │   └── main.tf
    │   ├── project
    │   │   └── main.tf
    ├── common
    │   └── prj-<company_name>-host
    ├── dev
    ├── hml
    ├── prod
    ├── foundation.tf
    └── variables.tf
